OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJapan rethinks tattoo ban  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fin defence forces          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Japan's defence force is rethinking a  
OL,6, ban on tattoos as it tries to increase 
OL,7, recruitment from a rapidly shrinking   
OL,8, population.                            
OL,10,FTattoos have long been a taboo in the  
OL,11,Fcountry, where they are associated with
OL,12,Fmafia-like criminal gangs known as     
OL,13,Fyakuza who sport elaborate skin art.   
OL,15,FBut officials now say that young       
OL,16,FJapanese sport tattoos for sartorial   
OL,17,Freasons, not to identify with yakuza.  
OL,19,FAnd they also argue that the ban is    
OL,20,Fhindering enlistment.                  
